T = int(input())
outputs = []

while(T > 0):
 
 inStr = input()
 inStr = list(map(int,inStr.split(" ")))
 finish = inStr[0]
 distancetoBolt = inStr[1]
 tigerAcceleration = inStr[2]
 boltSpeed = inStr[3]

 boltTime = finish / boltSpeed
 tigerTime = ((2 * (distancetoBolt + finish)) / tigerAcceleration) ** (1/2)
 if(tigerTime <= boltTime):
  outputs.append("Tiger")
 else:
  outputs.append("Bolt")
 
 T -= 1
 
print(*outputs, sep="\n")
